en_262864_0	The Cabinet of Ministers has granted approval to the proposed tax revisions put forward by the budget â€“ 2019.
en_262864_1	The Ministry of Finance states that the cabinet approval has been granted on revisions made to the Nation Building Tax and the Value Added Tax.
en_262864_2	If hotels, restaurants and businesses registered under the Sri Lanka Tourism Development Authority obtain funds from foreign sources through a local bank will be exempted from the Nation Building Tax.
en_262864_3	The Ministry of Finance said that importation of ships and boats for recreation and sports will also be exempted from the tax.
en_262864_4	The tax relief given to sub-contractors in the construction industry will also be given to the main contractor under the new revision.
en_262864_5	The new legislation will give relief to import of unprocessed gems and unrefined palm oil.
en_262864_6	The date to pay Value Added Tax will be shifted to the 20th day of the month for the convenience of the tax payers.
en_262864_7	The Value Added Tax levied on condominiums will also be revised.
en_262864_8	Accordingly, no tax will be charged on housing units cost less than 25 million rupees.
en_262864_9	The Ministry of Finance states that new amendments will be presented in Parliament in September following the completion of the drafting process.
